Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Mix first 3 ingredients until well blended; press onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan. Bake 8 min.; cool. Beat cream cheese, marshmallow creme and vanilla in medium bowl with mixer until well blended. Whisk in COOL WHIP; spread over crust. Refrigerate until ready to use. Add boiling water to gelatin mixes; stir 2 min. until completely dissolved. Stir in pineapple. Refrigerate 30 min. or until slightly thickened. Spoon over dessert. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.